### Theatres of [World War II](/World_War_II)

A truly global catastrophe, with various regions enduring their own unique brand of hell. Beyond the primary theatre we are discussing, the war spilled into:

#### Europe

*   [Poland](/Invasion_of_Poland): The initial victim, swiftly consumed by the [Soviet invasion](/Soviet_invasion_of_Poland).
*   The [Phoney War](/Phoney_War): A period of eerie calm before the storm, a testament to political indecision.
*   [Saar Offensive](/Saar_Offensive): A minor, almost forgotten, early skirmish.
*   [Finland](/Finland_in_World_War_II): Enduring the brutal [Winter War](/Winter_War), the [Continuation War](/Continuation_War) in [Karelia](/Continuation_War), and the [Lapland War](/Lapland_War).
*   [Weserübung](/Operation_Weser%C3%BCbung): Germany's swift occupation of [Denmark](/German_invasion_of_Denmark_(1940)) and [Norway](/Norwegian_campaign).
*   [Western Front](/Western_Front_(World_War_II)): The brutal campaigns through [Luxembourg](/German_invasion_of_Luxembourg), the [Netherlands](/German_invasion_of_the_Netherlands), [Belgium](/German_invasion_of_Belgium_(1940)), and the ultimate [Battle of France](/Battle_of_France). This included the [Italian invasion of France](/Italian_invasion_of_France) in the [Alps](/Italian_invasion_of_France) in 1940, and the [Second Battle of the Alps](/Second_Battle_of_the_Alps) in 1944–1945.
*   [Britain](/Battle_of_Britain): Defending its skies in the desperate [Battle of Britain](/Battle_of_Britain).
*   [Eastern Front](/Eastern_Front_(World_War_II)): The colossal, brutal struggle that included [Operation Barbarossa](/Operation_Barbarossa), the agonizing [Siege of Leningrad](/Siege_of_Leningrad), the [Crimean campaign](/Crimean_campaign), the grinding [Battles of Rzhev](/Battles_of_Rzhev), [Case Blue](/Case_Blue), the pivotal [Battle of Stalingrad](/Battle_of_Stalingrad), the largest tank battle at [Kursk](/Battle_of_Kursk), the vast [Dnieper–Carpathian offensive](/Dnieper%E2%80%93Carpathian_offensive), [Operation Bagration](/Operation_Bagration), the battles for [Romania](/Battle_of_Romania) and [Hungary](/Budapest_offensive), the [Vistula–Oder offensive](/Vistula%E2%80%93Oder_offensive), and the final, crushing [Battle of Berlin](/Battle_of_Berlin).
*   The subsequent [Liberation of France](/Liberation_of_France), spearheaded by [Operation Overlord](/Operation_Overlord) and [Operation Dragoon](/Operation_Dragoon).
*   The brutal grind of the [Siegfried Line campaign](/Siegfried_Line_campaign), the ambitious failure of [Operation Market Garden](/Operation_Market_Garden), the desperate German gamble in the [Battle of the Bulge](/Battle_of_the_Bulge), and the ultimate [Western Allied invasion of Germany](/Western_Allied_invasion_of_Germany).

#### [Asia-Pacific](/Pacific_War)

*   [China](/Second_Sino-Japanese_War): A long, forgotten struggle beginning with the [Marco Polo Bridge incident](/Marco_Polo_Bridge_incident), followed by the [Battle of Shanghai](/Battle_of_Shanghai), [Taiyuan](/Battle_of_Taiyuan), [Nanjing](/Battle_of_Nanking), [Xuzhou and Taierzhuang](/Battle_of_Xuzhou), [Wuhan](/Battle_of_Wuhan), the [1939–1940 Winter Offensive](/1939%E2%80%931940_Winter_Offensive), the [Hundred Regiments Offensive](/Hundred_Regiments_Offensive), the fierce fighting in [Northern Burma and Western Yunnan](/Battle_of_Northern_Burma_and_Western_Yunnan), [Operation Ichi-Go](/Operation_Ichi-Go), and the [1945 Hunan](/Battle_of_West_Hunan) campaign.
*   [Burma](/Burma_campaign): A series of brutal campaigns from [1941–1942](/Japanese_invasion_of_Burma), [1942–1943](/Burma_campaign_(1942%E2%80%931943)), [1944](/Burma_campaign_(1944)), and [1944–1945](/Burma_campaign_(1944%E2%80%931945)).
*   [South-East Asia](/South-East_Asian_theatre_of_World_War_II): Including the [Japanese invasion of French Indochina](/Japanese_invasion_of_French_Indochina), the [Franco-Thai War](/Franco-Thai_War), the [Japanese invasion of Thailand](/Japanese_invasion_of_Thailand), the [Fall of Hong Kong](/Fall_of_Hong_Kong), and the lightning campaigns in [Malaya and Singapore](/Malayan_campaign).
*   [South West Pacific](/South_West_Pacific_theatre_of_World_War_II): The bitter fighting in the [Philippines 1941–1942](/Philippines_campaign_(1941%E2%80%931942)) and [1944–1945](/Philippines_campaign_(1944%E2%80%931945)), the [Dutch East Indies campaign](/Dutch_East_Indies_campaign), the [Borneo 1945](/Borneo_campaign) campaign, the naval clashes at [Coral Sea](/Battle_of_Coral_Sea), the grueling [Solomon Islands campaign](/Solomon_Islands_campaign) (including [Guadalcanal](/Guadalcanal_campaign), [New Georgia](/New_Georgia_campaign), and [Bougainville](/Bougainville_campaign)), and the relentless [New Guinea campaign](/New_Guinea_campaign) (including [Kokoda Track](/Kokoda_Track_campaign), [Salamaua–Lae](/Salamaua%E2%80%93Lae_campaign), [Markham, Ramu and Finisterre](/Markham,_Ramu_and_Finisterre_campaigns), [Huon Peninsula](/Huon_Peninsula_campaign), [New Britain](/New_Britain_campaign), [Admiralty Islands](/Admiralty_Islands_campaign), and [Western New Guinea](/Western_New_Guinea_campaign)).
*   [Pacific Ocean](/Pacific_Ocean_theater_of_World_War_II): The decisive [Battle of Midway](/Battle_of_Midway), the island hopping through the [Gilberts and Marshalls](/Gilbert_and_Marshall_Islands_campaign), [Mariana and Palau](/Mariana_and_Palau_Islands_campaign), and [Volcano and Ryukyu](/Volcano_and_Ryukyu_Islands_campaign) Islands.
*   [Soviet-Japanese War (Mainland)](/Soviet%E2%80%93Japanese_War): Including the swift [Soviet invasion of Manchuria and Northern Korea](/Soviet_invasion_of_Manchuria) and earlier [pre-war border conflicts](/Soviet%E2%80%93Japanese_border_conflicts).
*   [Japan](/Japan_campaign): The final desperate battles in the [Volcano and Ryukyu Islands](/Volcano_and_Ryukyu_Islands_campaign), and the [Soviet invasions of South Sakhalin](/Soviet_invasion_of_South_Sakhalin) and the [Kuril Islands](/Invasion_of_the_Kuril_Islands).

#### [Mediterranean and Middle East](/Mediterranean_and_Middle_East_theatre_of_World_War_II)

*   [Balkans](/Balkans_campaign_(World_War_II)): The [Greco-Italian War](/Greco-Italian_War), the [German invasion of Greece](/German_invasion_of_Greece), the [Battle of Crete](/Battle_of_Crete), and the complex struggles in [Albania](/World_War_II_in_Albania) and [Yugoslavia](/World_War_II_in_Yugoslavia).
*   [Mediterranean Sea](/Battle_of_the_Mediterranean): The naval battles, the [Adriatic campaign](/Adriatic_campaign_of_World_War_II), the relentless [Siege of Malta](/Siege_of_Malta_(World_War_II)), and the [Dodecanese campaign](/Dodecanese_campaign).
*   [East Africa](/East_African_campaign_(World_War_II)): Including the [Italian guerrilla war in Ethiopia](/Italian_guerrilla_war_in_Ethiopia).
*   [Middle East](/Mediterranean_and_Middle_East_theatre_of_World_War_II): The [Anglo-Iraqi War](/Anglo-Iraqi_War), the [Syria–Lebanon campaign](/Syria%E2%80%93Lebanon_campaign), and the [Anglo-Soviet invasion of Iran](/Anglo-Soviet_invasion_of_Iran).
*   [North Africa](/North_African_campaign): The shifting sands of the [Libya-Egypt](/Western_Desert_campaign) campaigns, [Operation Torch](/Operation_Torch) in [Morocco-Algeria](/Operation_Torch), and the final push in the [Tunisian campaign](/Tunisian_campaign).
*   [Italy](/Italian_campaign_(World_War_II)): Beginning with the [Allied invasion of Sicily](/Allied_invasion_of_Sicily), followed by the [Allied invasion of Mainland Italy](/Allied_invasion_of_Italy), the brutal defensive stands along the [Winter Line](/Winter_Line) and [Gothic Line](/Gothic_Line), and the final [Spring 1945 offensive in Italy](/Spring_1945_offensive_in_Italy).

